external_data.name: An Allegory of Truth & Time
external_data.description: The scene is inspired by an old oil painting by the amazing Annibale Carracci - An Allegory of Truth & Time (c. 1584-85) - the story involves a few characters: Truth, Time, Deceit, Happy-End and Good-Luck. The moral of the painting would seem to correspond to two famous sayings (also current in English): 'The truth will out' and 'All's well that ends well'.

external_data.name: We are all Jerry
external_data.description:
Jerry is connected to the universe. We are all Jerry. 

He enjoys meditation, has a pet frog and plays the flute.

Jerry was designed in 2D, sculpted and animated in 3D and soundtracked with specially composed music just for him.

The winning bidder of Jerry will receive a high-resolution 4K loopable render, the very first original sketch, the colored concept art (first created in 2018) and the music track.

external_data.name: Torn #1
external_data.description:
The main abstract photo from my project ¬´Torn¬ª where I explore the beauty in shattered CDs.
By destroying the discs and photographing them up close, I give this dead-end technology new life‚Äîas psychedelic entertainment for the eyes. There is not a drop of any paint here, only the phenomenon of interference. My passion for abstract photography allows me to convey the feeling of how unreal, fantastic can be an ordinary subject from our everyday life.
7000x4670px jpg

external_data.name: Ethereal Blooms I
external_data.description:
This on-going series explores new 'digital painting' techniques. Using data harvested from artworks Leif created and processed into digital brush sets ‚Äì¬†These are then re-processed to create and capture new paintings in flux. 

Challenging the ideas of what painting is in a modern context, this series consolidates over 10 years work as a digital artist. Leif looks to push boundaries and redefine art in the modern age.
